A very casual and chill area to hangout with friends, have a meetup, or even get some light work done; Think of it as your neighborhood café meets Mediterranean hookah lounge.  PERKS -Music and TV not very loud; easy to have conversation with others -Hookah coal refills and the food (def try out the egg and pita dish (its not under the omelets section) I forget what it was called officially but it was absolutely amazing) -Staff and general ambience was very chill/busy medium.  Will def be the new "spot" for me when I hit up Brooklyn with friends!

If you want great hookah, this is your place. If you want amazing service from the hookah attendants and don't have to ask for coal refills this is also your place. However, there is a register worker who treats people he knows better than newcomers. Get on his good side and you're all set. The food is delicious for a hookah place. The music and ambiance on the other hand isn't too fun. It's wonderful in it's culture and beautiful in it's own way, but I'm not particularly interested in Arabic music while I'm out with the guys or brainstorming for a movie. Decor to match the music
